citation: Proclamation under the Veterinary Surgeons Amendment Act 2011 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Veterinary Surgeons Amendment Act 2011

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Veterinary Surgeons Amendment Act 2011 fix 12 December 2012 as the day on which the provisions of that Act commence.

3 December 2012

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

BRYAN GREEN

Minister for Primary Industries and Water

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 12 December 2012

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Primary Industries, Parks, Water and Environment.
